{"title_page": "Kenny Sebastian", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian stand-up comedian}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Kenny Sebastian\n| image              = Kenny 2016.jpg\n| caption            = \n| birth_name         = Kenneth Mathew Sebastian\n| birth_date         = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1990|12|31}}\n| birth_place        = [[Pala, Kerala|Pala]], [[Kerala]], India\n| home_town          = [[Bangalore]], [[Karnataka]]\n| occupation         = {{hlist|Stand-up comedian|Musician}}\n| years_active       = 2006 \u2013 present\n| known_for          = Stand-up comedy\n}}\n\n'''Kenneth Mathew Sebastian''' (born 31 December 1990), better known as '''Kenny Sebastian''', is an Indian [[stand-up comedian]], [[musician]] and [[filmmaker]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.knowkenny.com/kennybooking/|title=Kenny Sebastian \u2013 Profile|website=knowkenny.com|accessdate=15 August 2018}}</ref> He first rose to prominence through a [[YouTube]] channel that broadcasts clips of his stand-up shows, devotional song covers, in addition to original skits, garnering 152 million views since 2008. He has toured the [[United States]], [[Singapore]], [[Abu Dhabi]], [[Dubai]]<ref name=\":0\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/lifestyle/viral-and-trending/130516/make-way-for-kenny.html|title=Make way for Kenny|date=13 May 2016|work=Deccan Chronicle|access-date=24 October 2018}}</ref> and [[Australia]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.broadwayworld.com/australia-melbourne/article/Kenny-Sebastian-Announces-First-Australian-Shows-20180809|title=Kenny Sebastian Announces First Australian Shows|last=BWW News Desk|date=9 August 2018|work=Broadway World}}</ref> In 2017, he produced an hour-long comedy special for [[Amazon Prime]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/amazon-inks-ground-breaking-deal-14-indian-stand-up-comedy-specials-966401|title=Amazon Inks Groundbreaking Deal for 14 Indian Stand-Up Comedy Specials|last=Bhushan|first=Nyay|date=20 January 2017|work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref> He performs primarily in English, switching to [[Hindi]] for comic effect.\n\n==Personal life==\nKenny Sebastian was born on 31 December 1990 in [[Pala, Kerala|Pala]], [[Kerala]], India in a [[Catholic]] [[Malayali]] family and was brought up in [[Bangalore]].He did an art degree. His father was in the [[Navy]], hence Kenny migrated throughout his childhood. He posted a YouTube video introducing his father to superhero characters.A fun fact about him is that he is colour blind,he cant see shades of green and blue, not many people are aware of it. He speaks English, [[Malayalam]] (mother-tongue) and [[Hindi]].<ref name=\":0\" /><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/carry-on-kenny-sebastian-in-conversation-with-the-die-trying-comedian/article22836378.ece|title=Carry on, Kenny Sebastian: In conversation with the 'Die Trying' comedian|first=Susanna Myrtle|last=Lazarus|date=23 February 2018|newspaper=The Hindu}}</ref> He also has his own [[production house]] named SuperHuman Studioz. <ref>{{Citation|title=Chai Time Comedy with Kenny Sebastian : Being a Color Blind Painter.|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=P8wjHyhDs38|language=en|access-date=2019-08-12}}</ref> Kenny is also an undergraduate in painting. <ref>{{cite AV media |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Cdsnc70Un14 |title=Exams, CBSE, Punishments - Stand Up Comedy by Kenny Sebastian |work=Kenny Sebastian |publisher=[[YouTube]]|date=28 February 2016 }}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nKenny made songs from tweets, popularly known as ''#KennySing4Me''. This gained him his initial popularity.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/shayanroy/kenny-sing-4-me|title= KennySing4Me }}</ref> He also created an improvised sketch show for [[Comedy Central]] known as ''The Living Room''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.afaqs.com/news/media/42539_comedy-central-to-premiere-the-living-room|title=Comedy Central to premiere 'The Living Room'|website=afaqs!|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> He co-wrote and acted in the [[web series]] called ''Star Boyz''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eventseeker.com/artist/76831-kenny-sebastian|title=Kenny Sebastian - Artist Profile|last=|first=|date=|website=eventseeker.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=2020-03-17}}</ref> He did a [[cameo appearance|cameo]] in the web series ''Humorously Yours'', in ''Better Life Foundation'' by Naveen Richard and in ''Pushpavalli'' by [[Sumukhi Suresh]]. He also has an original series ''Die Trying'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/kenny-sebastian-die-trying-amazon-prime-5066515|title=  Die Trying actor Kenny Sebastian: It's painful to create music, stand-up is easier|date=17 February 2018}}</ref> an improvised show ''The Improvisers: Something From Nothing'' along with [[Abish Mathew]], [[Kanan Gill]] and [[Kaneez Surka]] and a [[sketch comedy]] show ''Sketchy Behaviour'' co-written and co-starring [[Kanan Gill]] on [[Amazon Prime Video]].He also started his mini series named \"Getting there\" which has 3 episodes. \n\nHe is a [[judge]] for ''[[Comicstaan]]'', a comedy hunt [[reality show]] on [[Amazon Prime Video]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/hindi/2018/jul/04/comicstaan-top-comics-kanan-gill-kenny-sebastian-sumukhi-suresh-others-to-redefine-future-of-f-1837776.html|title='Comicstaan': Top comics Kanan Gill, Kenny Sebastian, Sumukhi Suresh, others to redefine future of funny|website=The New Indian Express|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\nHe brings out videos from his standup routines and the occasional ''Chai Time With Kenny'' on his [[YouTube]] channel.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.republicworld.com/entertainment-news/bollywood-news/kenny-sebastian-a-stand-up-comedian-filmmaker-and-an-all-rounder|title=Kenny Sebastian: A stand-up comedian, filmmaker, and an all rounder|last=World|first=Republic|website=Republic World|access-date=2020-04-08}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Platform !! Name !! Notes \n|-\n| 2014 || rowspan=\"8\"| [[YouTube]] || Journey to the Center of My Brain || Himself\n|-\n| 2015 || Insides Out || Himself\n|-\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2016\n|Star Boyz <ref>{{Citation|last=Kenny Sebastian|title=3 South Indian Boys in Space {{!}} STAR BOYZ {{!}} CHAATS Ep 1 #LaughterGames|date=5 May 2016|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=p56_5T7oiFY|access-date=24 October 2018}}</ref>\n|Actor\n|-\n|A Door through a Window\n|Himself\n|-\n|Breezer Vivid\n|Alongside [[Abish Mathew]]\n|-\n| rowspan=2| 2017-2018 || rowspan=2| Son Of Abish \n| Season 2 with [[Radhika Apte]]\n|-\n| Season 4 with [[Yami Gautam]]\n|-\n|2017\u2013Present\n|Chai Time with Kenny\n|Himself\n|- \n|rowspan=2| 2017 || rowspan=2 |''[[Amazon Video]]''|| Don't Make That Face by Naveen Richard || [[Film director|Director]]\n|-\n| Don't Be That Guy<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.thehindu.com/todays-paper/tp-features/tp-metroplus/kenny-sebastian-dont-be-that-guy/article18188320.ece|title=Kenny Sebastian: Don't Be That Guy}}</ref>|| Himself \n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" |2018\n| rowspan=\"3\" |''[[Amazon Video]]''\n| Die Trying ||Kenny <ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/web-series/die-trying-kenny-sebastian-amazon-prime-review-5068017|title=Die Trying review: This Kenny Sebastian 'Brohemian Rhapsody' is enjoyable in parts|date=18 February 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/tv/die-trying-review-kenny-sebastian-s-amazon-show-is-a-middle-finger-to-middle-class-indian-establishment/story-9GrJ4QU6kX9PWViYdoEJdL.html|title=Die Trying review: Kenny Sebastian's Amazon show is a middle finger to middle-class Indian establishment|date=14 February 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|The Improvisers: Something From Nothing\n|Alongside [[Kanan Gill]], [[Abish Mathew]], [[Kaneez Surka]]\n|-\n|[[Comicstaan]]\n|Himself- Judge\n|-\n|